# granny-ro-js — local env config
#
# Default `npm test` (the JS-only content-addressed parity check + the
# unit tests) needs NONE of these. Copy to `.env` and fill in `RO_FOLDER`
# only if you want to run the wine + DLL live cross-check :
#
#   npm run bake            # extract .gr2 from data.grf + wine bake
#   npm run test:live       # wine + DLL → content-addressed manifest → JS verify
#
# See docs/HOWTO.md for the full setup walkthrough.

# REQUIRED for bake / test:live / rebake. Host path to your iRO ver12
# client. Must contain `data.grf` AND `granny2.dll`. Read-only — the
# scripts never write to this folder.
RO_FOLDER=/path/to/your/iRO_client

# OPTIONAL — override the command run by `docker compose run test`.
# Leave commented for the default (`npm test`, the JS-only contract).
# Uncomment for the full live wine path :
# TEST_COMMAND=npm run test:live

# OPTIONAL — override the wine binary used to launch the Win32 shim.
# Defaults to auto-detect :
#   - Linux       : `wine` on PATH (`sudo apt install wine`)
#   - macOS       : probes /Applications/Wine[ Staging].app/Contents/Resources/wine/bin/wine
#                   then /opt/homebrew/bin/wine, /usr/local/bin/wine, PATH
#   - Windows     : N/A — shim runs as native Win32 PE, no wine prefix
# Set explicitly only if your install isn't in the auto-detect list :
# WINE_BIN=/Applications/Wine Staging.app/Contents/Resources/wine/bin/wine

# OPTIONAL — override the path to granny2.dll. Defaults to
# ${RO_FOLDER}/granny2.dll. Set only if the DLL lives outside RO_FOLDER.
# GRANNY2_DLL=/path/to/granny2.dll

# OPTIONAL — override the prebuilt Win32 shim paths. Default to the
# committed binaries under shim/prebuilt/. The heavyweight Dockerfile
# sets these to /shim/... at image build time.
# GR2_IGC_EXPORT_EXE=/path/to/gr2_igc_export.exe
# GR2_DECOMPRESS_EXE=/path/to/gr2_decompress.exe
